;; mark_recursive_single_site.synth — recursive single-site
;; polymorphism targeting mark-type per 007 follow-up.
;;
;; Record T with a `data` field; two writes (int32 + float64)
;; to ONE T instance make the field CS-contour polymorphic.
;; walk(self: T) reads self.data and recursively dispatches
;; "walk" on itself. Main: single call site to walk(t).
;;
;; With the build_type_marks traversal fix, the polymorphic
;; field's marks propagate into walk's closure. The recursive
;; call edge re-enters walk's formal at a different mark
;; distance than main's direct edge. The hypothesis is that
;; stage 2 finds an ES-formal marked-confluence and splits via
;; mark-type. Golden documents what actually fires.

shape: mark_recursive_single_site
